WEBVTT

00:00:28.887 --> 00:00:32.704
He lives by himself in a home in Oxford
working late into the night,

00:00:32.728 --> 00:00:36.659
trying to unpack really,
the deepest mysteries of the cosmos.

00:00:37.508 --> 00:00:41.542
His thinking has really had
a dramatic impact on how I see the world.

00:00:41.953 --> 00:00:45.072
Here's the thing:
most scientists would tell you

00:00:45.096 --> 00:00:49.022
that human beings
just aren't that significant.

00:00:49.046 --> 00:00:52.609
We are just this little speck of dust
on a random planet,

00:00:52.633 --> 00:00:54.815
in an obscure part of the universe.

00:00:55.513 --> 00:00:58.077
David Deutsch says that's wrong.

00:00:58.664 --> 00:01:00.552
He actually says people matter,